A project where I am attempting to add fractals in lieu of a water texture in the original AR Sandbox project developed by Dr. Oliver Kreylos 
which you can find here: https://web.cs.ucdavis.edu/~okreylos/ResDev/SARndbox/

I absolutely love this project and have been building and maintaining AR Sandboxes for many years. This is one of my attempts to utilize CLaude LLM
and the CLine extension for VS Code to add a fractal visualisation on top of the original topographic simulation. 

*Currently this is not a working version and I will be returning to developing it further soon.*

The idea to add a fractal visualisation came from my old creative partner. He custom coded one of the coolest mods I've ever seen.
He added a Gray-Scott visualisation on top of the orginal topographic map simulation but it also had an interaction with the water simulation. 
The GS simulation could be seeded randomly by the press of a button and it utilized depth data in order to inform it's generation. It had the visual
effect of growing across the landscape and would change it's feed/kill and other values as the sand was moved by users. WILD STUFF!

Out of respect for him and his work I have been attempting to find my own way of adding a visualisation to this project as to not copy
his code or approach but this project is totally inspired by him. 

I'd give him accredidation but he has chosen not to publish that modification or display it himself. If that changes I'll ask his permission to link to it
as I consider this if not technically, very much spiritually a fork of his and Dr. Kreylos's work. 
